<title>NORWAY: ELKEM SEES 1997 DEMAND SAME AS 1996.</title>
<headline>ELKEM SEES 1997 DEMAND SAME AS 1996.</headline>
<dateline>OSLO 1997-08-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Norwegian metals producer Elkem ASA said on Tuesday it expected demand for its products in 1997 to be at about the same level as in 1996.</p>
<p>&quot;In the short term, the market for ferroalloys appears to be stable,&quot; Elkem said in a statement releasing half-year results.</p>
<p>&quot;For aluminium, the market has strengthened somewhat during the first part of the third quarter,&quot; it said.</p>
<p>Elkem booked first-half pre-tax profits down 14 percent from a axyear ago at 514 million crowns.</p>
<p>--Tanya Pang, Oslo newsroom, +47 22 42 50 41</p>
